The word Asbed or Aspet originially comes from the [[Armenian]] word for [[knight]]. It was later passed down in Armenian [[culture]] to become a give name for [[males]].


== History ==

== Asbed/Aspet Libardi ==
 
The history of the name was first recognised in 1373 AD when Asbed/Aspet Libardi one of Armenias great knights was killed. the story became a legend and the name of the knight became a household name (at the time).

The battle took place at a bridge on top of Antsmntsoog lake in Giligia in which Asbed/Aspet Libardi ordered his troops to defend the bridge on top of the lake while he went forward to drive the opposition away. after an intense battle the great knight tired and trying to return to the bridge reinforcements for the opposing force arrive and he fell to his death under the arrows of the opposition.--[[User:Abb401|Abb401]] 08:21, 18 September 2006 (UTC)